cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on the challenge of training deep neural networks with noisy labels, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for dealing with label noise, which could also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
